"When Iâ€™m in the middle of development and suddenly need to fix an urgent issue in another branch, I use git stash to temporarily save my current changes and switch branches safely."

###Save current (tracked changes) and clean working directory
git stash

###Save tracked + untracked files
git stash -u

###Show list of all stash entries
git stash list

###Apply (restore) stashed changes but keep stash in list
git stash apply

###Apply (restore) stashed changes and remove from stash list
git stash pop

###Delete a specific stash entry
git stash drop stash@{0}

###Delete all stash entries
git stash clear

